此站是一個高架車站，設有一個[[島式月台|島式月台]]、兩個停用的[[側式月台|側式月台]]和兩條軌道。軌道於此站月台北端的[[止衝擋|止衝擋]]結束。車站原先設計為[[西班牙式月臺佈局|西班牙式月臺佈局]]，下車乘客使用側式月台而上車乘客使用島式月台，但現時所有乘客都使用島式月台。

佩勒姆灣公園車站是唯一一個不使用號碼進行路軌編號的[[紐約地鐵|紐約地鐵]]總站，而採用方向進行標籤<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tricarico|first1=Michael|title=Track labels with service sign and 6 train on East track|url=http://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?29223|website=www.nycsubway.org|publisher=www.nycsubway.org|accessdate=2016-07-27|location=Pelham Bay Park|date=2004-04-12|archive-date=2019-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206141706/https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?29223|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 出口 ===
閘機位於月台下方的夾層。此站設有兩條樓梯、一條扶手電梯和一部升降機通往威斯徹斯特大道。同時車站入口亦設有一條行人天橋跨過布魯克納爾快速道路前往{{link-en|佩勒姆灣公園|Pelham Bay Park}}<ref name=maps>{{cite web|title=MTA Neighborhood Maps: Pelham Bay|url=http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bx/BX6_PelhamBay_2015.pdf|website=[[大都會運輸署|mta.info]]|publisher=[[大都會運輸署|大都會運輸署]]|accessdate=2016-07-20|date=2015|archive-date=2020-06-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605043820/http://web.mta.info/maps/neighborhoods/bx/BX6_PelhamBay_2015.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。升降機於2015年6月至2016年4月期間翻新<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/nyct/service/PelhamBayParkElevatorClosure_May2015.htm|title=mta.info {{!}} Station Information|website=web.mta.info|access-date=2016-03-25|archive-date=2019-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190917081407/http://web.mta.info/nyct/service/PelhamBayParkElevatorClosure_May2015.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 未興建的延線 ===
1968年紐約市擬定了{{link-en|行動計劃|Program for Action}}，作為該項目的一部分，佩勒姆線將延長至一個鄰近{{link-en|合作城 (布朗克斯)|Co-op City, Bronx|合作城}}的現代化總站，並將路線改為IND標準，令此站不再是總站<ref name="int-arch2">{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/metropolitantran00newy/metropolitantran00newy_djvu.txt|title=Full text of "Metropolitan transportation, a program for action. Report to Nelson A. Rockefeller, Governor of New York."|date=1967-11-07|website=Internet Archive|accessdate=2015-10-01}}</ref><ref name="nyc subway in the 1970s2">{{cite web|url=http://www.nycsubway.org/wiki/The_New_York_Transit_Authority_in_the_1970s|title=The New York Transit Authority in the 1970s|website=nycsubway.org|last1=Feinman|first1=Mark|accessdate=2015-04-23|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129032408/https://www.nycsubway.org/wiki/The_New_York_Transit_Authority_in_the_1970s|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="sas 1968">{{cite web|url=http://secondavenuesagas.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/06/1968expansionlarge.jpg|title=1968 NYCTA Expansion Plans (Picture)|publisher=Second Avenue Sagas|accessdate=December 2013|archive-date=2018-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009073021/http://secondavenuesagas.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/06/1968expansionlarge.jpg|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="joekorner 1968">[http://www.thejoekorner.com/lines/progforaction.htm Program for Action maps] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thejoekorner.com/lines/progforaction.htm |date=20170630171053 }} from thejoekorner.com</ref>。受1975－1976年紐約市財政危機的影響，大部分所餘下的計劃都缺乏資金，幾乎全數放棄。原先預計1970年代中至1980年代初完工<ref name="NYTimes-QBLExpansion-1971">{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=9A06E2D7103BE73ABC4951DFB466838A669EDE|title=New Line May Get Double Trackage: Transit Unit Shift on Queens Super-Express|date=1971-02-21|publisher=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|accessdate=2015-09-26|archive-date=2017-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913044046/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=9A06E2D7103BE73ABC4951DFB466838A669EDE|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYTimes-ArcherGrndbk-Oct1973">{{cite web|url=https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=9404E1D61631E63BBC4C51DFB6678388669EDE|title=Work Begun on Queens Subway Extension|date=1973-10-24|publisher=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|last1=Burks|first1=Edward C.|accessdate=2015-09-26|archive-date=2017-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909142941/http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=9404E1D61631E63BBC4C51DFB6678388669EDE|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但行動計劃受{{link-en|紐約市歷史 (1946-77)#1970年代|History of New York City (1946–77)#1970s|1970年代財政危機}}而縮減或取消<ref name="Raskin-RoutesNotTaken-2013">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CUlGCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA307|title=The Routes Not Taken: A Trip Through New York City's Unbuilt Subway System|date=2013-11-01|publisher=Fordham University Press|isbn=978-0-8232-5369-2|author=Joseph B. Raskin|accessdate=2015-08-12|archive-date=2017-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109100746/https://books.google.com/books?id=CUlGCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA307|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

